'''''Yankee''''' magazine was founded in 1935 and is based in [[Dublin, New Hampshire]], United States.
==History and profile== The first issue of the magazine appeared in September 1935.<ref>{{cite news|author=Sydney Ember|title=At 80, Yankee Magazine is Thriving as an Avatar of New England|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/10/05/business/media/at-80-yankee-magazine-is-thriving-as-an-avatar-of-new-england.html?_r=0|accessdate=September 4, 2016|work=The New York Times|date=October 4, 2015}}</ref> It is a bimonthly magazine devoted to [[New England]] travel, home, food and features. With a paid circulation of 317,000 and a total readership of nearly 2 million, it is published by Yankee Publishing Incorporated (YPI), one of the few remaining family-owned and independent magazine publishers in the United States. YPI also owns the oldest continuously produced periodical in the US, the ''[[Old Farmer's Almanac]]'', which it purchased in 1939.<ref name="yankeemagazine.com">{{cite web|work=Yankee Magazine|url=http://www.yankeemagazine.com/contact/aboutyankee/yankee-publishing|title=About Yankee Publishing|date=July 15, 2008|accessdate=January 10, 2013}}</ref> In 2013, YPI acquired McLean Communications, publisher of ''[[New Hampshire (magazine)|New Hampshire]]'' and the ''[[New Hampshire Business Review]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhbr.com/December-28-2012/Yankee-Publishing-buys-N.H.-Business-Review-N.H.-Magazine/|title=Yankee Publishing buys N.H. Business Review, N.H. Magazine|work=Nhbr.com|date=December 28, 2012|accessdate=December 2, 2013}}</ref> It is a member of the [[City and Regional Magazine Association]].<ref name="crma-members">{{cite web|url=http://www.citymag.org/City-and-Regional-Magazine-Association/Media-Partners/CRMA-Magazines/|title=CRMA Magazines|work=City and Regional Magazine Association|accessdate=October 14, 2013}}</ref>
